PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?population WHERE { <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Central_Greece_(region)> y2geoo:hasGAG_Population ?population }

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>

  <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Central_Greece_GRC.8.1_1> ?p ?population .

}

question: How much of the UK is woodland?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (( SUM(strdf:area(?fWKT)) / ?ukArea ) AS ?woodland) WHERE { yago:United_Kingdom geo:hasGeometry ?ukGeo . ?ukGeo geo:asWKT ?ukWKT BIND(strdf:area(?ukWKT) AS ?ukArea) ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?fGeo . ?fGeo geo:asWKT ?fWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?fWKT, ?ukWKT) } GROUP BY ?forest ?ukArea

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (SUM(?forestArea) AS ?woodlandArea) ?ukArea ?woodlandPercentage WHERE {
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/United_Kingdom> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasArea> ?ukArea .
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/United_Kingdom> <http://www.opengis.net/geo/hasGeometry> ?ukGeo .
  ?ukGeo <http://www.opengis.net/geo/asWKT> ?ukWKT .

  ?forest a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  ?forest <http://www.opengis.net/geo/hasGeometry> ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo <http://www.opengis.net/geo/asWKT> ?forestWKT .
  ?forest <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasArea> ?forestArea .

  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?forestWKT, ?ukWKT))
}
GROUP BY ?ukArea
BIND((?woodlandArea / ?ukArea) AS ?woodlandPercentage)

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (( strdf:area(?iWKT) / strdf:area(?niWKT) ) AS ?timesLarger) WHERE { yago:Republic_of_Ireland geo:hasGeometry ?iGeo . ?iGeo geo:asWKT ?iWKT . yago:Northern_Ireland geo:hasGeometry ?niGeo . ?niGeo geo:asWKT ?niWKT } LIMIT 1
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?ratio WHERE {
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland> <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/hasArea> ?areaIreland .
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Northern_Ireland> <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/hasArea> ?areaNI .
  
  # Extract numeric part of areaIreland (remove #m^2)
  BIND(xsd:double(REPLACE(STR(?areaIreland), "#m\\^2", "")) AS ?areaIrelandNum)
  
  # Extract numeric part of areaNI (remove #m^2)
  BIND(xsd:double(REPLACE(STR(?areaNI), "#m\\^2", "")) AS ?areaNINum)
  
  # Compute ratio
  BIND((?areaIrelandNum / ?areaNINum) AS ?ratio)
}

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?dimos WHERE { yago:Agia_Paraskevi geo:hasGeometry ?o . ?o geo:asWKT ?geoWKT . ?dimos rdf:type y2geoo:GAG_Municipality ; geo:hasGeometry ?geomC . ?geomC geo:asWKT ?cWKT FILTER geof:sfTouches(?geoWKT, ?cWKT) }

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?municipality WHERE {

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?stream WHERE { yago:Thessaly geo:hasGeometry ?lgeo . ?lgeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT . ?county rdf:type y2geoo:GAG_Municipality ; geo:hasGeometry ?geo . ?geo geo:asWKT ?WKT . ?stream rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_stream ; geo:hasGeometry ?sgeo . ?sgeo geo:asWKT ?sWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?WKT, ?lWKT) FILTER geof:sfCrosses(?WKT, ?sWKT) }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?stream ?streamWKT WHERE {
  # Thessaly geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Thessaly> geo:hasGeometry ?thessalyGeo .
  ?thessalyGeo geo:asWKT ?thessalyWKT .
  
  # Municipality and its geometry
  ?municipality a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_Municipality> .
  ?municipality geo:hasGeometry ?municipalityGeo .
  ?municipalityGeo geo:asWKT ?municipalityWKT .
  
  # Thessaly contains municipality
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(?thessalyWKT, ?municipalityWKT))
  
  # Stream and its geometry
  ?stream a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_stream> .
  ?stream geo:hasGeometry ?streamGeo .
  ?streamGeo geo:asWKT ?streamWKT .
  
  # Stream crosses municipality
  FILTER(geof:sfCrosses(?streamWKT, ?municipalityWKT))
}

  # Bay is of class OSM_bay

  ?bayGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?bayWKT .

gold_query:

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>

  ?streamGeo geo:asWKT ?wkt .

  # The stream is within the Republic of Ireland
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?streamGeo, ?roiGeo))

  # There exists another stream that intersects this stream (indicating tributary relation)
  ?otherStream rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_stream> .
  ?otherStream geo:hasGeometry ?otherStreamGeo .

}

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?stream ?streamWKT WHERE {
  # Tullyhaw Barony geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Tullyhaw> geo:hasGeometry ?baronyGeo .
  ?baronyGeo geo:asWKT ?baronyWKT .
  
  # Streams in Tullyhaw Barony
  ?stream a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_stream> .
  ?stream geo:hasGeometry ?streamGeo .
  ?streamGeo geo:asWKT ?streamWKT .
  
  # Townlands
  ?townland a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSI_Townland> .
  ?townland geo:hasGeometry ?townlandGeo .
  ?townlandGeo geo:asWKT ?townlandWKT .
  
  # Stream is contained in Tullyhaw Barony
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?streamWKT, ?baronyWKT))
  
  # Stream is west (left) of townland
  FILTER(strdf:left(?streamWKT, ?townlandWKT))
}

SELECT DISTINCT ?townName ?lakeName WHERE { ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSI_Townland ; y2geoo:hasOSM_Name ?townName ; geo:hasGeometry ?cityGeo . ?cityGeo geo:asWKT ?cityWKT . ?vilg rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; y2geoo:hasOSM_Name ?lakeName ; geo:hasGeometry ?vilgGeo . ?vilgGeo geo:asWKT ?vilgWKT . yago:Republic_of_Ireland geo:hasGeometry ?IrGeo . ?IrGeo geo:asWKT ?IrWKT FILTER ( ( geof:sfContains(?IrWKT, ?cityWKT) && geof:sfContains(?IrWKT, ?vilgWKT) ) && geof:sfTouches(?cityWKT, ?vilgWKT) ) }

  ?lake <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?lakeGeo .
  ?lakeGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?lakeWKT .

  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland> <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/sfContains> ?lake .

question: Which city has the largest park in Texas?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?city (strdf:area(?parkWKT) AS ?area) WHERE { yago:Texas geo:hasGeometry ?usaGeo . ?usaGeo geo:asWKT ?usaWKT . ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city ; geo:hasGeometry ?cityGeo . ?cityGeo geo:asWKT ?cityWKT . ?park rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_park ; geo:hasGeometry ?parkGeo . ?parkGeo geo:asWKT ?parkWKT FILTER ( geof:sfContains(?usaWKT, ?parkWKT) && geof:sfContains(?cityWKT, ?parkWKT) ) } ORDER BY DESC(?area) LIMIT 1

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?city WHERE {
  # Texas contains the park
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Texas> <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/sfContains> ?park .
  
  # The park is contained in the city
  ?city <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/sfContains> ?park .
  
  # The city is of class OSM_city
  ?city a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_city> .
  
  # The park is of class OSM_park
  ?park a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_park> .
  
  # Get the area of the park
  ?park <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/yago2geo#hasArea> ?area .
}
ORDER BY DESC(?area)
LIMIT 1

question: Which counties are east of County Kerry and west of County Wexford?

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?x WHERE { { ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSI_County_Council } UNION { ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSI_City_and_County_Council } ?x geo:hasGeometry ?gx . ?gx geo:asWKT ?xWKT . yago:County_Wexford geo:hasGeometry ?gy . ?gy geo:asWKT ?yWKT FILTER strdf:left(?xWKT, ?yWKT) yago:County_Kerry geo:hasGeometry ?gz . ?gz geo:asWKT ?zWKT FILTER strdf:right(?xWKT, ?zWKT) }

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?county WHERE {
  {
    ?county a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OS_County> .

question: Which regional unit in the region of Thessaly has a beach?

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?city WHERE { yago:Thessaly geo:hasGeometry ?THGeo . ?THGeo geo:asWKT ?A . ?city rdf:type y2geoo:GAG_RegionalUnit ; geo:hasGeometry ?geomC . ?geomC geo:asWKT ?C . ?beach rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_beach ; geo:hasGeometry ?geomB . ?geomB geo:asWKT ?B FILTER ( geof:sfWithin(?C, ?A) && geof:sfWithin(?B, ?C) ) }

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?regionalUnit ?regionalUnitWKT WHERE {
  # Thessaly region
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Thessaly> geo:hasGeometry ?thessalyGeo .
  
  # Regional unit contained in Thessaly
  ?regionalUnit rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_RegionalUnit> .
  ?regionalUnit geo:hasGeometry ?regionalUnitGeo .
  ?regionalUnitGeo geo:asWKT ?regionalUnitWKT .
  
  # Thessaly contains the regional unit
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?regionalUnitGeo, ?thessalyGeo))
  
  # Regional unit contains a beach
  ?beach rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_beach> .
  ?beach geo:hasGeometry ?beachGeo .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?beachGeo, ?regionalUnitGeo))
}

PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>

  ?county a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OS_County> .

  # Spatial containment: county contains lake

  FILTER(geof:sfContains(<http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/geoentity_Great_Britain_2648147>, ?county))

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE { ?m rdf:type y2geoo:GAG_Region . yago:Corfu geo:hasGeometry ?cg . ?m geo:hasGeometry ?mg . ?cg geo:asWKT ?cw . ?mg geo:asWKT ?mw FILTER strdf:below(?mw, ?cw) ?l rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?lg . ?lg geo:asWKT ?lw FILTER geof:sfWithin(?lw, ?mw) }

PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE {
  # Corfu geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Corfu> geo:hasGeometry ?corfuGeo .
  ?corfuGeo geo:asWKT ?corfuWKT .
  
  # Regions and their geometries
  ?region a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_Region> .
  ?region geo:hasGeometry ?regionGeo .
  ?regionGeo geo:asWKT ?regionWKT .
  
  # Forests and their geometries
  ?forest a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  ?forest geo:hasGeometry ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo geo:asWKT ?forestWKT .
  
  # Region is south of Corfu
  FILTER (strdf:below(?regionWKT, ?corfuWKT))
  
  # Region contains forest
  FILTER (geof:sfContains(?regionWKT, ?forestWKT))
}

question: Can you determine the names of the lakes in Greece that are completely encompassed within a single municipality?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?l WHERE { ?m rdf:type y2geoo:GAG_Municipality ; geo:hasGeometry ?mg . ?mg geo:asWKT ?mw . ?l rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?lg . ?lg geo:asWKT ?lw FILTER geof:sfWithin(?lw, ?mw) }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?lakeName WHERE {
  # Get Greece geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Greece> geo:hasGeometry ?greeceGeo .
  ?greeceGeo geo:asWKT ?greeceWKT .
  
  # Get lakes and their geometries
  ?lake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
  ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeo .
  ?lakeGeo geo:asWKT ?lakeWKT .
  
  # Lake is within Greece
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?lakeWKT, ?greeceWKT))
  
  # Get municipalities and their geometries that contain the lake
  ?municipality a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_Municipality> .
  ?municipality geo:hasGeometry ?municipalityGeo .
  ?municipalityGeo geo:asWKT ?municipalityWKT .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(?municipalityWKT, ?lakeWKT))
  
  # Get lake name
  ?lake <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?lakeName .
}
GROUP BY ?lake ?lakeName
HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?municipality) = 1)

  # United States geometry

  ?usGeo geo:asWKT ?usWKT .
  
  # Forests in the United States
  ?forest a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  ?forest geo:hasGeometry ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo geo:asWKT ?forestWKT .

question: Can you identify the woodland areas in the districts situated to the south of Staffordshire?
gold_query:

SELECT DISTINCT ?district WHERE { yago:Staffordshire geo:hasGeometry ?Staffordshire_geo . ?Staffordshire_geo geo:asWKT ?Staffordshire_geoWKT . ?district rdf:type y2geoo:OS_District ; geo:hasGeometry ?district_geo . ?district_geo geo:asWKT ?district_geoWKT FILTER strdf:below(?district_geoWKT, ?Staffordshire_geoWKT) ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?forest_geo . ?forest_geo geo:asWKT ?forest_geoWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?forest_geoWKT, ?district_geoWKT) }

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

  BIND(<http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Staffordshire> AS ?staffordshire)

  ?staffordshire geo:hasGeometry ?staffordshireGeo .

PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>

  # Oregon entity
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Oregon> geo:hasGeometry ?oregonGeo .
  ?oregonGeo geo:asWKT ?oregonWKT .

  # Lakes in Oregon
  ?lake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
  ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeo .
  ?lakeGeo geo:asWKT ?lakeWKT .

  ?stream geo:hasGeometry ?streamGeo .

  # Lakes and streams are contained in Oregon

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?municipality ?municipalityName WHERE {
  ?municipality <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_Municipality> .
  ?municipality <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasGAG_Population> ?population .
  FILTER(?population < 3000) .
  
  ?municipality <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasGAG_Name> ?municipalityName .
  
  ?island <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_island> .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(<http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Nisan>, ?municipality)) .
  FILTER(geof:sfContains(?municipality, ?island)) .
}

  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Central_Macedonia> geo:hasGeometry ?centralGeo .
  ?centralGeo geo:asWKT ?centralWKT .
  
  # Municipality of type GAG_Municipality with geometry
  ?municipality a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/GAG_Municipality> .
  ?municipality geo:hasGeometry ?municipalityGeo .
  ?municipalityGeo geo:asWKT ?municipalityWKT .
  
  # Municipality population and name
  ?municipality <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasGAG_Population> ?population .
  ?municipality <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasGAG_Name> ?name .

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?forest) AS ?forests) WHERE { ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?x1Geo . ?x1Geo geo:asWKT ?x1WKT . ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?x2Geo . ?x2Geo geo:asWKT ?x2WKT FILTER geof:sfTouches(?x1WKT, ?x2WKT) }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?forest) AS ?numForests)
WHERE {
  ?forest a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  ?forest <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?forestWKT .
  
  ?lake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
  ?lake <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?lakeGeo .
  ?lakeGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?lakeWKT .
  
  FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?forestWKT, ?lakeWKT))
}

question: How many canals intersect with lakes in the United States?

question: How many canals in England are west of villages in Camrbridgeshire?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) AS ?canals) WHERE { yago:Cambridge geo:hasGeometry ?oGeo . ?oGeo geo:asWKT ?oWKT . yago:England geo:hasGeometry ?eGeo . ?eGeo geo:asWKT ?eWKT . ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_canal ; geo:hasGeometry ?xgeo . ?xgeo geo:asWKT ?xWKT . ?y rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_village ; geo:hasGeometry ?ygeo . ?ygeo geo:asWKT ?yWKT FILTER ( ( geof:sfContains(?eWKT, ?xWKT) && geof:sfContains(?oWKT, ?yWKT) ) && strdf:left(?xWKT, ?yWKT) ) }

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>

WHERE {

  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/England> geo:hasGeometry ?englandGeo .
  
  # Bind Cambridgeshire and get its geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Cambridgeshire> geo:hasGeometry ?cambridgeshireGeo .
  
  # Get villages in Cambridgeshire
  ?village a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_village> .
  ?village geo:hasGeometry ?villageGeo .
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?villageGeo, ?cambridgeshireGeo))
  
  # Get canals in England
  ?canal a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_canal> .
  ?canal geo:hasGeometry ?canalGeo .
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?canalGeo, ?englandGeo))
  
  # Filter canals west of villages
  FILTER(strdf:left(?canalGeo, ?villageGeo))
}

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?forest ?area ?forestWKT WHERE {
  # Essex geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Essex> <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?essexGeo .
  ?essexGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?essexWKT .

  # Forests of class OSM_forest with geometry and area
  ?forest a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  ?forest <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?forestWKT .
  ?forest <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasArea> ?area .

  # Spatial overlap filter
  FILTER(geof:sfOverlaps(?forestWKT, ?essexWKT))
  
  # Subquery to get minimum area of overlapping forests
  {
    SELECT (MIN(?a) AS ?minArea) WHERE {
      ?f a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
      ?f <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?fGeo .
      ?fGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?fWKT .
      ?f <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasArea> ?a .
      FILTER(geof:sfOverlaps(?fWKT, ?essexWKT))
    }
  }

  # Filter forests to those with minimum area
  FILTER(?area = ?minArea)
}

question: Which city in England is adjacent to the most lakes?

SELECT ?city WHERE { yago:England geo:hasGeometry ?eGeo . ?eGeo geo:asWKT ?eWKT . ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city ; geo:hasGeometry ?cGeo . ?cGeo geo:asWKT ?cWKT . ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?lGeo . ?lGeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT FILTER ( geof:sfWithin(?cWKT, ?eWKT) && strdf:touches(?cWKT, ?lWKT) ) } GROUP BY ?city ORDER BY DESC(COUNT(?lake)) LIMIT 1

question: What is the largest forest in Texas by area?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?forest (strdf:area(?fWKT) AS ?farea) WHERE { yago:Texas geo:hasGeometry ?usGeo . ?usGeo geo:asWKT ?usWKT . ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?fGeo . ?fGeo geo:asWKT ?fWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?fWKT, ?usWKT) } ORDER BY DESC(?farea) LIMIT 1
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?forest ?name ?area ?wkt WHERE {
  # Get Texas geometry
  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Texas> <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?texasGeo .
  ?texasGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?texasWKT .
  
  # Get forests of type OSM_forest
  ?forest <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .
  
  # Get forest area
  ?forest <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasArea> ?area .
  
  # Get forest name
  ?forest <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/hasOSM_Name> ?name .
  
  # Get forest geometry
  ?forest <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?wkt .
  
  # Filter forests located within Texas
  FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?wkt, ?texasWKT))
}
ORDER BY DESC(?area)
LIMIT 1
